This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with action recognition from video sequences. The use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and convolutional neural networks (CNNs) also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The mention of optical tracking data and video data suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of SVM for classification suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
